caption: Good price for great quality food. Very consistent and fast delivery.
Nice scene for thai food. Got there about one, it wasn't busy. The service was very friendly and kind. Prices are reasonable I would say. Atmosphere and food reminds me of Virginia Beach.

So yummy. When I eat the food I feel like I could hug the chef. It really feels like It’s made with love and delivered from a land far away. it’s so authentic and flavorful. This sounds cliche AF but I’m finally writing about this place and I’ve order from them possibly 50 times this past year. They got me and my coworkers thru the pandemic as nurses with delicious food. The food comes piping hot and is perfectly spicy. I love it. I just wish there was another location because this is close to my job. But I know food like this can’t be replicated. It’s sooooo good. I can’t say this enough. The drunken noodle is the best I’ve had. Fried rice on point. Perfect sizes. Pricing great. Not many foods can I eat 3 times in one week but it’s that good.
thai food and the atmosphere at this place is excellent. Had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again. The prices are fair for the quality of food.

Horrible experience with Living Thai, I wish I could give them 0 stars. I placed a delivery order through Seamless that was supposed to arrive within 25-35 minutes and it never showed up. After 1 hour of waiting, I called the restaurant to check on the status of the delivery. The restaurant kept insisting that the food had been delivered and they called my cell phone, however I NEVER received a phone call or text message, there was no food to be found in the lobby of my building, and the doorman had confirmed there was no food delivered in the timeframe that the restaurant insisted. I explained this to Living Thai and they were legit acting crazy on the phone, shouting at me, and refusing to give me a refund for the order. Shame on this restaurant for lying that food was delivered and shame on them for screaming through the phone about it. I will never eat at this place or order from them again. They did nothing to remedy the situation and they are a disgrace with horrible customer service.
Luncheon special of coconut soup with chicken, and shrimp vegtables was superb!
Ordered takeout. Pad Thai and Drunken Noodles were delicious. Five stars.
Spice level extremely high. Tom kha was amazing.

I order to take out off the lunch menu. The service was quick and the food was really flavorful! My friend got the Pad Thai and I got the Drunken Noodle. We got a nice portion of food and were super satisfied with the meal.

I visit this excellent restaurant from time to time because I enjoy the good air that is outline this place. The personel is exceptionally friendly and experienced. The service is absolutely efficient. Also, the food they serve is good. I ate there many times and I was always satisfied. The pay is modest. I suggest this place to all my friends.

Their food is nice. However, they modified the tip amount. This happened quite a few times. I didn’t notice this until one day I looked at my statement carefully. This is absolutely intolerable! I never went there again since that. Be extremely careful!
Favorite Thai place in the area! The drunk noodles are fantastic (better than their Pad Thai). I’ve only used them for delivery so no idea what their service is like

The food was delicious!  Fresh and perfectly seasoned with just the right amount of heat.  The curry was especially good, as was the Basil Chicken.  Delivery was fast.  Will definitely order from here again!
Really, in these times of Covid-19, finding a hair in my food is not very comforting. Come on. Delivery was quick and food was tasty, bit the hair ruined my dinner.

On 4/15. I carried 3 big luggage and 1 carry on and 1 duffel bag downstairs. One Latino man was outside talking on the phone. All of a sudden, he offered to help me to carry all my luggage downstairs even I wore a mask and he did not wear any protection. Then he told me he worked in the restaurant- LivingThai next door and asked me when would my cab arrive? I thought he was waiting too because he kept looking at the street after I said I called the cab. To my surprise, once my Via came, he just picked up all my luggage and lifted them up to the cab while the driver was not willing to help in the beginning（totally understandable so I gave him hand sanitizers after he dropped me off). I was so grateful and I offered him tips but he was shocked and just smiled at me and shake his head. It turned out he was not waiting for his cab and he just waited to help me out! I am so blessed and this is the most beautiful memory and a farewell gift from NYC during Covid-19. Hope everyone is safe in America! We are in this together! Always be kind to others.
Picked up take out haven’t been here in a few months. Food was great. Will be back again.
Decent food. It's byob which is great.

Called the restaurant because the deliver is late. The receptionist said I have to understand it’s a weekend and tried to give me a lecture. Not even said Sorry. What a great customer service. No more ordering from you.
The go-to Thai restaurant in the neighborhood! The food is consistent, delicious, and reasonably priced for the portion. I love how the restaurant can turn up the spice level as I like :)

We tried one noodle dish and one rice curry dish.   The prices are the best in the area, but then again the rice portion for take-out was about a third the amount of a typical take-out container. The texture of the noodles was chewy and nice. Unfortunately we found both the dishes to to be quite bland.
Nice place
i'm in new york for a vacation and i can tell you i went there four times already. you eat very well and the staff very generous and delicious.
Love their lunch specials, yummy food
Great food And people

I celebrated my PhD last night in this great restaurant. I am glad to say that it was a phenomenal evening and the venue was absolutely one of the reasons for this successful celebration. The waiters  helped in a graceful style, the meals were very good and my buddies were extremely  pleased. We shall surely return for more events. thanks very much.

We like a lot to go out. Last night we arrived in this magnificent restaurant which friends told us about. We passed a beautiful experience there with first-rate dishes and a well-trained stuff and a great  chef. We put this venue in our list  and we will certainly come back soon. We highly recommend.
The food is always delicious and made fresh (always piping hot whether I dine-in or take-out). Very friendly service. My favorite Thai place in the area!
Friendly, welcoming, and great food.
Nice food for great price .
Excellent food and gives new meaning to the word "spicy". Absolutely delicious
Good flavor
Great food and excellent service. One of the best Thai restaurants in the city.
Great!

Thai food is so authentic! The spice and everything is just perfect. Staff is very nice and the environment is clean. Can't wait to come back again to try other food from the menu. Hopefully they will have my fav dessert available next time!
Not very good food but definitely huge portion and good service
Great Thai foodand gread friendly service. We had the basil noodles, pineapple fried rice, and chicken gyoza. The decorations in the restaurant ere fun
It’s the best place to have Thai food. The place is very clean, the food is amazing and super healthy
Tried here once. Probably not again
Decent food, but expect long wait times.
I live nearby and come here a lot - never disappointed!

(Translated by Google) The shopkeeper is kind .. .. own food .. delicious food .. Thai taste .. eat and miss home Very much .. come to New York, don't forget to stop by.  (Original) เจ้าของร้านใจดี..รับแขกเอง..อาหารอร่อย..รสชาติไทยๆ..ทานแล้วหายคิดถึงบ้าน ฟินมากครับ..มานิวยอร์คอย่าลืมแวะนะครับ.

Amazing Thai place with delicious food. Loved the experience and the food. The waitresses were super friendly and efficient. Highly recommend this to anyone looking for some genuine Thai food at economic prices. Definitely going to come here again when I am back in nyc :)

Just went to this place for lunch.  Food is good, they give an entree and an appetizer for under 9 dollars. Friendly staff and a comfortable place to have a casual lunch.  Go and take a date or a family.
Veggie rice. Tea n spring rolls 😋

This place cares more about making money than customer satisfaction. Our order was incorrect and they were not willing to fix it. When we told them that that’s not what we ordered, they insisted we pay additionally for the items we actually wanted- which we refused to do. We’re now leaving with a meal that we had to pay for and do not want/ will not eat. As a waitress, I would NEVER do this to my customers. Terrible service.

Horrible service. Will never go again. We were lied to multiple times and the food we ordered was not what we wanted. They forced us to pay for the food and had no concern to make the situation right. Who does that?? We asked to speak to a manager and they told us they don’t have a manager. Stay away from this place, they will rip you off
AMAZING!
Decided to try a new Thai spot for lunch since they closed down my favorite one & the experience was EXCELLENT ♥️.
Amazing food . The pineapple Fried rice was so good . And their fried ice cream is great too.
The prices were modest, but the dishes were fresh and flavorful, and the service was friendly and prompt. We'll definitely come back.
I eat here at least twice a month. I love the red curry with tofu. The service is excellent here.

Wonderful addition to the neighborhood!  The food is excellent and very fresh, well prepared. I've eaten here 3 times and was consistent each time. Pad Thai is the barometer for good Thai food and theirs is quite good!  It's a relaxed, clean and comfortable place. The waitress was friendly, and they even played cool Brazilian jazz!  Much better than other Thai in the area!

Very good food and customer service. Basil fried rice and drunken noodles were amazing. We ordered vegetarian and they were caring enough to replace a soup that had fish sauce in it even without asking. Highly recommended!
There are many new Thai restaurants opening in this neighborhood,  but this one stands out among the Asian restaurants around, because the food is fresh which in itself makes it tasty and fulfilling.
Food is fairly good, and priced very well.
Great food, absolutely recommendable. Got the Lunch special Chicken red curry and pork dumplings for only $8.00. Filling and delicious.
My new favorite Thai restaurant in the area!! Their lunch special is only $8 (and goes until 4:30 PM) I always get the basil dish with pork and Tom Yum soup!
Really lovely food and ambience. Great lunch time deal.
Amazing food, attentive staff, quick turnaround. Love it. Deserves more business.

Great, humble little Thai place on the UWS! Happy it's here, we'll be back for sure. Nice vibe inside with good music and cute photos on the walls.  We ordered: - spring rolls - chicken pad Thai - Thai basil duck - mango sticky rice dessert  Would recommend all of these. The duck was my favourite, had nice flavor and a good heat. Pad Thai was good, more on the sweet side if that's your pad Thai preference.
Lunch is cheap. Food is fine.
Great experience. Recommend. Will be back!
Shrimp with mixed vegetables. Absolutely delicious. Top of the line food and service. Do yourself a favor and come!

Better food and service than at competitor Thai Market a few blocks away.   They have a good lunch special.  The interior of the restaurant and the tables are all very clean.  If I had one criticism to offer, I thought the dishes had a bit too much salt.  Both my Tom Kha soup and Drunken Noodles would have been better with a bit less salt.  Other than that, I look forward to trying other dishes here in the future.
Love it! Delicious, very reasonably priced, adorable, just the best Thai option around here!
Nice food

I tried one stir beef with beans (I forgot the name but they are literally what inside the dish), it was pretty good. The beef is juicy and tender, with a lot of flavor in it. I also ordered the Thai ice tea, and it is authentic. The restaurant has good lunch special, maybe stop by next time.
Good and delicious, staff was so kind (2 gender neutral bathrooms!!!!!!)
